The people of this area mainly depend upon agriculture product. But the flood of July'2019 make the road unfit for all type of vehicles as well as the pedestrian. So to restore the communication to carry relief materials to the flood effected areas palisading, sand fill begs pitching, bamboo foot Bridge and minimum quantity of gravel is provided in this estimate.

Repairing/renovation work in the office building of O/o the Joint Director of Surveys, Assam, Dakhingaon, Guwahati-40.
column10: The existing office of the Joint Director of Surveys, Assam is Assam type building which is very important office where all records of land survey, map etc. are stored. This office consists of three nos. of of Assam type buildings connecting with corridor passage which are in very deplorable condition due to non-repairing of three buildings since a long period of time, for which doors and steel casement windows & ventilation, partition walls, ceiling etc. are badly damaged due to rusting and termite action. This estimate has been prepared as one building (building No 1) in consultation with Joint Director and Assistant Directors for urgent repairing/renovation of the same including alternation and modification of interior rooms, toilets etc
column15: Establishment Expenditure

column9: There are six number of existing staff quarters namely type A & B of grade-III inn the office of the Principal, ASSTC. The existing quarters of office of the Principal, ASSTC are in very deplorable condition due to non repairing since a long time for which most of the the items i.e. flooring, doors, windows, plastering, roofing, painting, sanitary and water supply are badly damaged and not at all fit for human inhabitation. So it is very essential for repairing the same for proper functioning of the building.

column1: Digital Cadastral Map for the Whole State of Assam (Procurement of High Resolution Satellite Image for the Entire State of Assam).
column9: The objective of this project is to get satellite image for the entire state of Assam which is most accurate, reliable, and timely data, which is essential in land use change detection, precision farming, emergency response, social research among other applied fields. Being up-to-date with the evolving technologies, there is a need to procure HRSI satellite images, with highest resolution available, for the entire state of Assam for proper mapping of the individual land ownership as well as to have a comprehensive map of Assam for use in PM-GATI Shakti as a base layer.

column1: Procurement of Machinery and Trolley Mounted Pumps for mitigation of urban flooding of Guwahati city under SDRF for the year 2024-25
column9: Procurement of Machinery and Trolley Mounted Pumps for mitigation of urban flooding of Guwahati city under SDRF stated as follows: 1. Procurement of Trolley Mounted Centrifugal pumps: 6 (Six) Nos. of 350 LPS & 4 (Four) Nos. of 150 LPS capacity 2. Procurement of Amphibian Excavator cum Dredger: 1 Time period for execution- 1 year
column10: 1. The pumps will aid in mitigation of urban flooding of Guwahati city. 2. The trolley mounted portable dewatering pumps is driven by diesel engine and thus make the pumps flexible to install in the water logging areas. 3. Due to shortage of portable dewatering pumps the agencies like GMC/GMDA is facing inconvenient in discharging the accumulated water from the submerged areas. 4. Amphibian Excavator cum Dredger will be engaged for periodic de-siltation and excavation of water bodies viz. Silsako Beel, Borsola Beel & Bondajan Beel for increasing the retention capacity and free flow of storm water.

(For Nagaon & Kamrup district)
column9: Resilient Relief Camp on Wheels in 02 flood prone districts on a pilot basis is envisaged as an alternate solution for shelter to reduce the basic hurdles (viz. Waste Management, Sanitation, Power, Water Hygiene, Community kitchen, Fire Safety, Alternate education etc.) faced by the inmates residing in the temporary camp/camp like situation during disaster. (For Nagaon & Kamrup district)
column10: OUTCOMES OF THE PROJECT: Mitigate chances of evolution of epidemic, famine based on SDG-3 Availability of clean water and sanitation to meet up the goal define in SDG-6 &13. Meet up clean energy and communication as per SDG 7 and point number 8 of PMs 10 point agenda. Ensure basic education among the children in the MRCs under SDG 4. Maintain the gender equality define under SDG 4. Ensure safety and resilience of the inmates from secondary disaster as per SDG 11
